---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Section from '../../components/Section.astro';
import Button from '../../components/Button.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Content Authority Audit"
  description="Topic-level competitive gap analysis. Every question your audience asks, mapped against what you and your competitors actually answer."
>
  <Section class="pt-28 pb-16">
    <div class="max-w-3xl">
      <p class="text-accent font-mono text-sm mb-4">The Get Right &rsaquo; Content Authority Audit</p>
      <h1 class="mb-6">Content Authority Audit</h1>
      <p class="text-accent text-lg font-medium mb-4">Powered by Canary</p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-xl leading-relaxed">
        Topic-level competitive gap analysis. We identify every question your audience
        is asking, crawl your site and your competitors, and show you exactly where
        they're answering and you're not.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section elevated>
    <h2 class="mb-8">What we examine</h2>
    <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Topic Discovery</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Questions your audience asks across search, forums, and social</li>
          <li>Topic clustering at the theme level (never keyword-level)</li>
          <li>Search intent mapping per topic cluster</li>
          <li>Volume estimation at the cluster level for prioritization</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Competitive Coverage</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Your content mapped against discovered topics</li>
          <li>Competitor content mapped against the same topics</li>
          <li>Coverage gaps: topics they answer that you don't</li>
          <li>Authority gaps: topics you both cover but they do better</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Content Health</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Thin content detection</li>
          <li>Content decay analysis (aging, outdated information)</li>
          <li>Internal linking gaps and orphaned pages</li>
          <li>Duplicate and cannibalization detection</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-bg-surface border border-border-subtle rounded-lg p-6">
        <h4 class="text-accent mb-3">Strategic Synthesis</h4>
        <ul class="text-secondary-text space-y-1.5 text-base">
          <li>Prioritized content roadmap by gap severity</li>
          <li>Content briefs for top-priority topics</li>
          <li>Internal linking recommendations</li>
          <li>Content refresh and retirement priorities</li>
        </ul>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mb-4">Topics, not keywords</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        We don't track keyword rankings. We don't report on keyword difficulty.
        We don't care about individual keyword volume.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        Canary operates at the <span class="text-primary-text">topic level</span>.
        A topic is a cluster of related questions your audience asks. The analysis
        reveals whether you're answering those questions comprehensively &mdash;
        and whether your competitors are doing it better.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg">
        This is a fundamentally different approach from tools like SEMrush or Ahrefs.
        Those tools tell you which keywords to target. We tell you which questions
        your brand needs to answer to build authority.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section elevated>
    <div class="max-w-2xl">
      <h2 class="mb-4">How it connects</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-6">
        Content gaps don't exist in isolation. Missing structured data from the
        Platform Technical Audit means your existing content isn't visible. Measurement
        gaps from the Revenue Performance Audit mean you can't tell which content
        is actually driving conversions.
      </p>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg">
        The Content Authority Audit maps the opportunity. The other two pillars
        ensure you can actually capture it.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section>
    <div class="text-center">
      <h2 class="mb-4">See the full picture</h2>
      <p class="text-secondary-text text-lg mb-8 max-w-xl mx-auto">
        Content is one of three pillars. The Get Right runs all three simultaneously
        and synthesizes them into one execution plan.
      </p>
      <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-4">
        <Button href="/the-get-right">See The Full Get Right</Button>
        <Button href="/contact" variant="secondary">Talk to a Founder</Button>
      </div>
    </div>
  </Section>
</BaseLayout>
